1
00:00:00,380 --> 00:00:03,703
The restoration happened in 1965

2
00:00:04,868 --> 00:00:06,254
From 1965 to 1969

3
00:00:10,853 --> 00:00:13,506
Interviewer: Since that date

4
00:00:13,818 --> 00:00:19,099
Did the restoration efforts preserve the church’s original architecture, or did they alter it?

5
00:00:19,483 --> 00:00:22,556
No, they did not change anything, it remained as it was

6
00:00:23,938 --> 00:00:27,238
So the church was thriving and exemplary

7
00:00:31,583 --> 00:00:33,736
All the families used to come here regularly

8
00:00:34,060 --> 00:00:37,446
On Fridays, and on Sundays they came

9
00:00:37,738 --> 00:00:40,791
And religious holidays were observed here

10
00:00:42,002 --> 00:00:43,068
That is what there was

11
00:00:43,740 --> 00:00:46,919
The church was vandalized

12
00:00:48,070 --> 00:00:49,843
Due to the military operations

13
00:00:53,207 --> 00:00:58,739
Because of the military operations, it was shelled with rockets and other munitions

14
00:01:01,380 --> 00:01:05,781
Interviewer: We mean before ISIS took control

15
00:01:06,092 --> 00:01:09,028
That is, before that time

16
00:01:10,773 --> 00:01:15,619
Was it subjected to destruction, war crimes, or disasters?

17
00:01:16,252 --> 00:01:17,351
You mean how long before?

18
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:21,506
Interviewer: Before ISIS entered Mosul, that is, before 2013

19
00:01:21,573 --> 00:01:22,573
No, no

20
00:01:23,277 --> 00:01:27,083
And in particular we Armenians are known

21
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:31,580
For self-financing, and we do all the work ourselves

22
00:01:31,972 --> 00:01:36,546
Through the Central Committee in Baghdad

23
00:01:37,674 --> 00:01:42,480
According to our means, we managed all the churches that belong to us

24
00:01:43,128 --> 00:01:45,788
In 1914

25
00:01:46,813 --> 00:01:48,226
When did ISIS enter?

26
00:01:51,383 --> 00:01:53,429
Interviewer: In 2014 Witness: Yes, in 2014

27
00:01:54,510 --> 00:01:57,616
They stayed here for three years, in this church

28
00:01:57,757 --> 00:01:59,796
I do not know what they did with it

29
00:02:02,309 --> 00:02:03,429
Until it was liberated

30
00:02:04,309 --> 00:02:07,743
We went in and saw the church completely wrecked

31
00:02:08,463 --> 00:02:10,143
We do not know what they were doing with it

32
00:02:10,531 --> 00:02:13,813
Interviewer: Okay Mr. Abu Ari, you say we do not know what happened to it

33
00:02:14,022 --> 00:02:18,201
Did you not hear from anyone that they made this place

34
00:02:18,553 --> 00:02:20,733
It is obvious, do you not see?

35
00:02:21,177 --> 00:02:22,177
That it was for detention and holding

36
00:02:22,838 --> 00:02:26,465
There must have been a court here or something like that

37
00:02:26,673 --> 00:02:28,739
It is clear from the footage

38
00:02:31,830 --> 00:02:38,453
A detention center belonging to ISIS, they kept prisoners here, I do not know

39
00:02:38,887 --> 00:02:42,526
I do not know about it, so I cannot tell you anything, I did not see it

40
00:02:47,293 --> 00:02:52,353
Interviewer: Mr. Abu Ari, who is now in charge of the restoration efforts related to the church?

41
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:54,475
And is there a plan to restore it?

42
00:02:56,340 --> 00:02:57,434
We want you to tell us the details

43
00:02:57,480 --> 00:03:04,878
I am responsible for the churches, buildings, and monasteries adjacent to the church

44
00:03:05,421 --> 00:03:09,341
If no organizations come to rebuild, it will remain like this

45
00:03:12,127 --> 00:03:15,113
And we do not have the capacity to do construction and rebuilding

46
00:03:15,446 --> 00:03:16,533
Except through support from an organization

47
00:03:18,428 --> 00:03:21,952
Interviewer: Okay, is there a plan for the future

48
00:03:22,152 --> 00:03:25,730
Or in the coming days to restore this place?

49
00:03:26,318 --> 00:03:28,151
I do not know when they will come

50
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:31,971
No one has come to us. What can I tell you?

51
00:03:35,095 --> 00:03:36,694
No organization has come to us

52
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:40,500
Interviewer: What is the reason?

53
00:03:40,540 --> 00:03:43,489
Only people from the Christian Endowment came

54
00:03:44,898 --> 00:03:48,768
They inspected the church and the hall

55
00:03:49,289 --> 00:03:51,926
And they said there was no budget available

56
00:03:52,624 --> 00:03:55,096
We are waiting for the budget to be issued so they can rebuild it
